Couple took their son out of Sweyne Park School in Essex without permission for a five-day holiday to Spain . 
  They were originally fined £120 for the unauthorised absence from the school in November 2014 . 
  They failed to pay after being convicted of failing to ensure their child regularly attended school . 
  Court bailiffs visited the family and demanded £1,230 for the holiday . 
  The boy’s grandmother paid up to stop the bailiffs taking property to cover the fine . 
 